<br>
Mudfish looked down from the notice pinned up in the Shar Vahl tavern to the young -- and not-young -- scaled wolf at his side.  The horned beast was wriggling its whole body and scuffling the floor with its front claws, as it was wont to do when excited.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Food!  Stories!  Songs!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  The warder nipped at a loose edge in the Iksar's tattered hopperhide armor.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Drink!  We must go!  We must, we must, we must!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Mudfish sighed and reached down, gently prying the scaled wolf's jaws apart.  &quot;We can't,&quot; he told it.  &quot;It's in Freeport.  They'll kill us if we even go close.&quot;<br>
<br>
The scaled wolf stopped wriggling and looked mournful.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kill orcs?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Mudfish shook his head.  &quot;I tried that.  It didn't make any difference.&quot;  Turning away from the notice, he hefted his pack and slouched toward the door.<br>
<br>
The warder whined softly, looking back at the notice, then trotted after its master (and ward).<br>
<br>
Failed again, it thought to itself, in the part of itself that was private from the bond it shared with the young, doleful Iksar.  Oh, well.  One day... <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
